            <main_text>
                <p>
                    <s>The graph shows the orbital period and planet radius of more than three thousand real exoplanets.</s> 
                    <s>Both the <m>x</m>-axis and <m>y</m>-axis scales are logarithmic.</s> 
                    <s>The <m>x</m>-axis shows the orbital period of the exoplanet in <unit form="word/plural">day</unit>, and 
                    the <m>y</m>-axis shows the radius of the planet as a multiple of the radius of Jupiter.</s>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <s>A Hot Jupiter is an exoplanet that has a mass and a planet radius similar to or slightly larger 
                    than those of Jupiter but also has an orbital period of less than 
                    <quantity><value>10</value><unit form="word/plural">day</unit></quantity>.</s> 
                    <s>Which of the regions labeled on the graph shows where Hot Jupiters appear?</s>
                </p>
